checksum: don't inline exported functions

We can't allow functions which consumers may rely on to be inlined;
this causes build failures in consumers.

Same patch as at https://src.fedoraproject.org/rpms/libnids/raw/rawhide/f/libnids-1.24-inline.patch.

Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/818517
Signed-off-by: Sam James <sam@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
Update the patch to track established connections

This should now apply correctly.

fix the crash of function nids_killtcp()

nids_killtcp() will crash after nids_init() is called for the second
time in the same process, because of the static initialization of
variable tcp_tag and ip tag.

Merge pull request #1 from f-s-p/master

Sane default tcp_flow_timeout

Sane default tcp_flow_timeout

Rather than turning off the new feature, use a sane default value of 1 hour, which should cover most firewalls' and OS's TCP idle timeout.

Add timeout for TCP streams.

Submitted by:	Frank Poz

Initial import.

This is a direct import of libnids-1.24.tar.gz from
http://libnids.sourceforge.net.
